  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: During the last load testing session we found out that when a chat has received lot of long messages, it starts to slow down. Typing or navigating back takes couple of seconds. When a different chat is opened, it works fine. When the app is killed and the long chat is opened again it also works fine (probably memory was flushed when app was killed).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nOnly recently seen messages are kept in RAM so that there is enough memory for the app to work fast.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe app slowes down if there is significant number of long messages in a chat.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nThere is no easy steps to reproduce. I tried to sent 30 messages 1-1 messages (each ~200 words long) but the chat still worked fine on my device.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.26\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
